comments.body:
@nikic Thanks for the elaborate comment! I experimented on your suggestions. 

Few things came up. 

1) "should not push to UserChain in extractDisjointBitsFromXor" The thing is distributeCastsAndCloneChain() expects a constant at the end of the chain, breaking that invariant means doing a major refactor of this pass from my vantage point, also It's not clear to me how that would work. So I'm trying to be conservative about the fix, overall the pass itself seems overly complex in design and easy pitfalls in correctness all over the place. 
```
if (ChainIndex == 0) {
    assert(isa<ConstantInt>(U));
    // If U is a ConstantInt, applyCasts will return a ConstantInt as well.
    return UserChain[ChainIndex] = cast<ConstantInt>(applyCasts(U));
  }
````

2) ``` unsigned OpNo = (BO->getOperand(0) == UserChain[ChainIndex - 1] ? 0 : 1); ``` we can make this much more explicit and choose OpNo based on non-constant operand of the BO but we may still run into BO's that have both operands as constants, in which case it's ambiguous what has to be done ( fall back to this comparison for a start maybe? ) 

3) "Isn't this already handled by the code below, which will create a XOR with the adjusted operand (containing only the non-disjoint bits). I expect the fix to adjust when this code path is taken (or removing it entirely)." Well it screws up the correctness in this case for non-zero XOR LHS constants. So not taking this approach.
